(40, 21, 29, 23, 1, 16, 19, 'repented, and went', 'Repentance and Obedience', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance and the call to obedience. In Matthew, the son initially refuses but later repents and acts, while Isaiah emphasizes the need for willingness and obedience to receive blessings.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
