(40, 22, 30, 46, 7, 29, 31, 'neither marry, nor are given in marriage', 'Temporal vs. Eternal Perspectives', 'Both passages emphasize the transient nature of earthly relationships and possessions. Matthew highlights the lack of marriage in the resurrection, while 1 Corinthians advises a detachment from worldly ties, indicating a focus on the eternal.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
